Ad Text:
The Business
  

Boutique, business that is highly regarded and enjoys an excellent reputation in the financial advisory sector
Committed to the provision of excellence which shows in all aspects of their operations and client delivery
Highly qualified team servicing platforms, the IFA sector and licensees
Continued and steady grown has meant that an opportunity has been created for an experienced and passionate Investment Analyst to join the business to perform fund manager research and analysis with gradual exposure to other asset classes
Professional working environment and down-to-earth team will provide excellent exposure and experience and opportunity to grow within a broader wealth management context
Small team ensures you get a broad and extensive exposure to all facets of the investments division and direct access to clients also
  
The Role
  

Working closely with both the investment and advisory team and reporting directly to the CIO, you will provide in-depth quantitative analysis and reporting
Maintain a focus on fund manager research
Implement highly successful investment opportunities that meet the needs of the client groups
Monitor and continually analyse existing investments and manage investment risk
Part of the role will see you responsible for all the reporting, compliance requirements and investment administration so it is imperative that you have strong attention to detail and an appetite for this kind of work
Attend and present to the investment committee and maintain good working relationships with fund managers and industry bodies
Maintain databases and information sources to ensure they are up to date and accurate
  
The Candidate
  

Tertiary qualified individual with a real interest and passion for investment markets and a strong technical background
Ideally 3-5 years’ experience and commencement of the CFA program is ideal but not essential
Previous exposure to investment analysis is vital - gained either in investment management, research house or private banking
Extensive experience using Excel and ideally you are an advanced user
Motivated, energetic with a positive attitude and a hunger to learn and contribute
A definite team player who is keen to work on a broad range of activities – not just the numbers
Strong verbal and written communication abilities with a sound understanding of the structure of reports
Attention to detail and accuracy in your work are essential

Salary: $700-$900 pd inc super depending on experience
Ad Text:
Company Background

Join a premier Australian infrastructure organisation that is currently undergoing a period of major capital investment. This company operates as a high-energy, fast-paced hub where smart problem-solvers to solve complex issues. You will be part of a team driven to do things better, backed by inspiring leaders and a supportive environment dedicated to professional growth.

About The Role

As a Portfolio & Benefits Analyst, you will play a central role in the Benefits & Investment Assurance team, focusing on the integrity and performance of the company’s capital investments. You will bring independent rigour to major proposals, ensuring all projects are strategically aligned and evidence-based. Your work will bridge the gap between Strategy, Finance, and Delivery, providing the insights needed to maximize value across the entire portfolio.

This role will be a 12 month daily rate contract role with strong chance of extension / permanent conversion.

Key Responsibilities

Benefits Identification: Identify, quantify, and establish baselines for both financial and non-financial benefits across the capital portfolio.
Realisation Monitoring: Track and monitor the ongoing realisation of benefits to ensure major investments deliver the intended value to the organisation.
Portfolio Assurance: Conduct regular health checks and reviews to assess delivery confidence across the capital portfolio.
Investment Analysis: Review business cases, risk registers, and delivery strategies to ensure accuracy and strategic alignment.
Stakeholder Engagement: Facilitate structured interviews with project sponsors and managers to gather evidence and test core assumptions.
Strategic Reporting: Draft clear reports with actionable recommendations for senior decision-makers regarding investment performance.




About You

Experience: You possess 3+ years of experience in benefits analysis, portfolio analysis or investment assurance
Technical Knowledge: You have a strong grasp of capital governance and major project delivery methodologies
Analytical Rigour: You are skilled at linking individual project outcomes to broader strategic objectives and portfolio goals.
Communication: You can simplify complex investment data into clear insights for senior stakeholders.
Curious Mindset: You bring a collaborative approach and the confidence to constructively challenge assumptions.
Industry Insight: Background in infrastructure is highly desirable.




Company Culture

This is a collaborative environment where passionate experts readily share knowledge and work together to bring an exciting vision to life. They value taking ownership of actions, and adapting to change. They currently have a hybrid working policy in place with 3 days per week in the office (a short train journey from the CBD)

We’re looking for a skilled Analyst to join the Benefits & Investment Assurance team and help drive evidence-based decision-making across this Real Estate & Infrastructure Asset Managers capital portfolio.

In this role, you’ll analyse, track and report financial, operational, sustainability and compliance benefits to ensure investment outcomes are realised and aligned with our strategic priorities.

What you’ll do

Maintain the Benefits Register and portfolio dashboards
Analyse project and portfolio benefits, highlighting trends, risks and variances
Support Post Implementation Reviews by validating realised outcomes
Prepare regular and ad-hoc benefits reports for governance forums
Provide insights on portfolio trade-offs, dependencies and strategic alignment
Contribute to planning cycles and continuous improvement of benefits frameworks
What you’ll bring

Degree in Business, Economics, Data Analytics, Engineering, Project Management or similar
2–5 years’ experience in benefits management, portfolio analysis financial analysis or project reporting
Strong analytical capability including dashboarding (Power BI or similar)
Understanding of project delivery and assurance frameworks (Stage Gates, PMBOK, PRINCE2)
Excellent communication and reporting skills
Please apply immediately to make your interest known ideally for a December start date.

Company description:



About VIDA

About VIDA The Victorian Infrastructure Delivery Authority (VIDA) is a specialist project delivery organisation, responsible for delivering the biggest transport and health infrastructure program in Victorian history. This includes more than 200 projects such as the Metro Tunnel, North East Link, West Gate Tunnel, removing level crossings, new and upgraded hospitals in Footscray, Frankston and Warrnambool, and specialist programs.



Job description:



About VIDA Health

VIDA Health (Victorian Health Building Authority) is responsible for the rollout of the Victorian Government's multi-billion-dollar health capital projects. We're delivering world-class health facilities across Victoria including new public hospitals and emergency care, community health services, ambulance branches, residential aged care and mental health facilities. VIDA Health also provides technical support across engineering, property, asset management and environmental sustainability disciplines.

The Opportunity

As Manager, Project Data Governance, you will lead a team of analysts within the Project Controls branch to ensure project data is accurate, consistent, well-governed and fit for purpose. Your work will underpin critical internal and external reporting to senior executives, Ministers, central agencies and the public.

This is a senior leadership role focused on establishing strong data governance frameworks, driving quality and assurance across project reporting, and enabling meaningful insights through modern analytics and visualisation tools.

Working closely with project teams, Reporting & Analytics, and key stakeholders across VIDA and government, you will ensure project data supports informed decision-making across the full project lifecycle.


Key aspects of the role include:

Establishing and maintaining data governance standards, definitions and quality frameworks for project data.
Leading a team of analysts to deliver high-quality insights and dashboards using tools such as Power BI.
Overseeing the coordination, quality assurance and delivery of monthly project and program reporting.
Supporting external reporting, ministerial briefs and audit requirements with defensible, accurate data.
Driving innovation and continuous improvement across project data, reporting and governance practices.
Ensuring compliance with legislative, privacy and information security requirements.

We are looking for:

A data governance or reporting leader with experience in complex, enterprise-scale environments.
Strong expertise in data quality, governance frameworks and assurance processes
Experience working with analytics and reporting platforms such as Power BI, Excel/Power Query, SharePoint and SQL-based environments.
Proven ability to translate complex data into clear insights for executive and non-technical audiences.
A confident leader who builds capability, influences stakeholders and drives continuous improvement.

To learn more about the opportunity and view the full requirements please download a copy of the Position Description HERE.

Qualifications
Tertiary qualification in data governance, business, analytics, risk, project management or a related discipline, or demonstrated equivalent professional experience.
Experience within project controls, PMO or large infrastructure delivery environments will be highly regarded.

Interested in working with VIDA Health?

Please click the "Apply" button to submit a copy of your resume and a cover letter expressing your interest and suitability for the role.

We don't want you to miss out! Please only apply for this position via the "Apply" button as emailed applications will not be considered.

Applications close 11.59pm on Thursday the 12th of February.

If you require any adjustment to the recruitment and selection process or need an alternative format to any of the application material, please contact TalentPeopleandCapability.vhba@vida.vic.gov.au.

Further information

Want to know more about VIDA Health? Check out our website and LinkedIn.

VIDA Health is an equal opportunity employer, committed to fostering a values-led, diverse and inclusive workplace. We believe our teams should represent the diversity of our communities in which we work, and we actively embrace and celebrate people from all walks of life.

All prospective employees undergo a National Criminal Records Check. You must be an Australian Citizen or Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa. Preferred candidates will be subject to pre-employment checks including, but not limited to, police checks, reference checks, qualification checks and role related clearances.

Job Title: Senior Data Modeller - 12 Month Max Term Contract
Ad Text:
Opportunity to work with one of the largest General Insurer in Australia

Open to Sydney candidates only - Hybrid opportunity

An impactful role to deliver solutions for the Data Platform

About Hollard

Hollard Insurance is part of the Hollard Group of Companies and a top 5 General Insurer in Australia and New Zealand. We underwrite a broad range of general insurance products, including motor, home, contents, business, and pet. Hollard’s unrelenting focus on diversity and inclusion, collaborative partnerships, and delivering great customer outcomes is at the heart of its business model, driven by its purpose of “Using our expertise, integrity and humanity to go further, together" 

Your team

You'll be joining the Chief Data Analytics Office (CDAO), who help enable drive data-driven decision making across Hollard. You will be surrounded by data professionals that strive for excellency and data best practices to realise business value. You will have the opportunity to apply your knowledge and experience to drive change and development as part of the CDAO team

Your role

 This role will actively build on Hollard’s Data Platform and see you developing and maintaining the Enterprise Data Model guided by industry data standard and following regulatory requirements. 

You will also be responsible for maintaining the design and documentation of conceptual, logical and physical data model solutions for the Hollard Data Platform and Consumption Layer, including relational, dimensional, and data lake structures. The solutions will support enterprise information management, business intelligence, analytics, real-time data sharing and other business requirements.

Your duties and responsibilities

Reporting to the Enterprise Data Architecture Lead, the key focus areas will be:

Responsible for the development of conceptual, logical, and physical data models, the implementation of RDBMS, operational data store (ODS), data marts, and data lakes on target platform. STAR STAR Schema and 3NF modelling knowledge is desirable.

Responsible for the source-to-target mapping and maintaining related documentation. 

Engage business users and SME’s to understand data requirements and translate those requirements into design.

Enhance and own the Enterprise Data Model defining key data domains and sub-domains, establishing definitions and maintaining versioning.

Review the business process and conceptualize the entities into the data model that interoperate within the business process.

Define and govern data modelling and design standards, tools, best practices, and related development for enterprise data models

About You

Demonstrated experience on relational, dimensional, and/or analytic experience (using RDBMS, dimensional, NoSQL data platform technologies, and ETL and data ingestion protocols). .

Hands on experience modelling for ODS data lakes, data warehouse, data marts, and enterprise big data platforms is required.

Good knowledge of metadata management, data modelling, and related tools (Erwin or ER Studio or others) required.

Must have the ability to work independently and collaboratively to address project requirements and articulate issues/challenges to reduce project delivery risks.

Knowledge of insurance industry standard ACORD model is a plus.

Working at Hollard

At Hollard, you’ll discover an environment where you can truly make an impact. We offer the best of both worlds – the opportunity, agility and creativity of a company growing with scale, alongside a focus on becoming a catalyst for enduring, positive, social change. 

We’re a tight-knit team, where authentic voices and unique perspectives matter. We work supportively, collaboratively and inclusively to help shape our future and create shared value for our communities. 

Hollard proudly promotes flexible work including remote work, non-traditional work patterns, and work-family balance. We’re also unapologetically committed to creating a workplace that values your diversity with a true sense of inclusion.  We actively seek to hire for your different lived experiences, including as it relates to disability, ethnicity, faith, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, gender diversity, sexual orientation, age, neurodiversity. 

We’re building something special. Working closely with our industry partners to reshape insurance for the better, we’re people changing insurance. 

Please note:  

Even if you don’t meet all our selection criteria, we encourage you to apply.  

A full background check will be completed on the successful applicant. 

Visit the Hollard careers page to learn about how Hollard will collect, store and handle your personal information.  

We are NOT engaging Recruitment Agencies for this role and ask agencies to respect our policy of no unsolicited contact regarding advertised vacancies.

About the role 

We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Data Engineer to join our Data and Insights team in a 12 months Fixed Term Contract. This role is critical in the ongoing administration, enhancement, and optimisation of our enterprise data platforms. People First Bank (PFB) currently operates on-premise data warehouses and is progressively building a modern Data and Insights capability.

This role is offered as a 12 months Fixed Term Contract with potential permanency or extensions.

Key Responsibilities:

Liaise with business departments to evaluate and determine data needs and requirements. Apply technical and analytical skills to solutions to improve PFB  reporting, advanced analytics, and data insights.
Work with Business Intelligence Analysts, Data Base Administrators, Business Analysts, IT and other key stakeholders to, maintain, organise and improve data warehouse solutions. Assist in the development of future business intelligence strategy and data governance decisions for PFB.
Maintain effective commercial relationships with external service providers to deliver optimal data management and reporting outcomes for the business.
Engineer & model curated Data Warehouse solutions to support BI objectives and timeframes in relation to the development of key analytics and metrics 
Partner with technical teams to build maturity and capability in relation to implementing data capture, ETL, validation, and test methods
Participate in an on-call support roster to help monitor, maintain, and troubleshoot the Data and Insights platform, ensuring high availability and reliability of critical data services.
Maintain and assist in data model documentation, data dictionary, data flow, data mapping and other MDM and Data Governance documentation




About you 

You are the go-to experts in crafting, implementing, and sustaining resilient data processing pipelines. Your role is pivotal in guaranteeing the effectiveness, precision, and scalability of our data infrastructure, impacting not only the Data and Insights team but also extending across the entire organization.

Knowledge and Experience:

Extensive experience in a similar role within a complex data environment.
Strong hands-on experience with ETL tools, preferably SSIS and WhereScape.
Advanced SQL skills, including the ability to write complex queries using sub-queries, nested queries, and other advanced SQL techniques.
Proficient in the Microsoft BI stack, including SSAS, SSRS, and SSIS, with additional exposure to Power BI for reporting and dashboarding.
Experience with CDC (Change Data Capture) tools, specifically Precisely, for real-time and incremental data movement.
Experience working with Azure DevOps, including Git repositories and Azure Pipelines; familiarity with PowerShell scripting and Power BI deployment.
Solid understanding of enterprise data warehouse (EDW) methodologies, including data analysis, data modelling, data integration, and data warehouse design.




Who are we? 

It's an exciting time to join our organisation! On 1 March 2023, two of Australia's most successful member-owned banking organisations merged to form People First Bank – powered by Heritage and People's Choice.  We are Australia's leading mutual banking organisation and a genuine, member-owned alternative to the major banks. 

We exist to create a better future for our members and the communities in which they live. 

We are 100% member owned, with approximately 720,000 members and 1,900 employees. We have dual head offices in Adelaide and Toowoomba, and 95 branches across South Australia, Victoria, New South Wales, Queensland and the Northern Territory, trading under two brands, Heritage Bank and People's Choice. 

When you come to work with us, you'll be joining a team of inclusive, friendly, and motivated employees who value making a difference every day for our members, community, and the planet. We are committed to creating an outstanding working environment where you feel supported, can continue to develop and are proud advocates of our members and our business.  




Benefits of working for us  

We believe the little extras can make a big difference in supporting your success. That's why we offer great incentives and benefits including: 




Extensive range of financial and lifestyle benefits, including (but not limited to): 

Paid parental leave and special leave provisions 
Flexibility and hybrid working arrangements
Employee banking benefits and discounted insurances 
Career development opportunities, and ongoing training, coaching and support 
A dedicated Employee Assistance Program for you and your family to access in times of need 
Paid volunteering days and access to a diverse range of community and charitable initiatives 




If you are ready to join a supportive team who are passionate about the work they do and the results they achieve, then apply now.




If this sounds like you, then this is the next step in your career. Click 'Apply' now and submit your application, including a cover letter and current resume by 15th February 2025.

Company: Sharp & Carter Technology, Projects & Digital Brisbane
Ad Text:
Project Manager | Contract till June 30 (possible extensions)
Brisbane CBD + WFH
 
A large enterprise organisation  is executing a multi-year digital transformation, moving away from legacy and in-house systems toward a sophisticated ecosystem of SaaS platforms, underpinned by a new integration layer and is seeking a Project Manager to lead the initiation/planning stage of the automated testing and test data management capability project.
 
The Project Manager will support preparation of business case and execution planning for program approval that will ensure secure handling of sensitive data and effective testing practices across multiple SaaS platforms.
 
What you'll be doing:

Lead project planning phase of automated testing and test data management capability project.
Work with SME's to define overarching test strategy and associated tooling, standards, and practices
Integrate test strategies with environment and release management plans
Coordinate internal teams, vendors, and SMEs to deliver across multiple platforms
Support preparation of business case and execution planning for program approval
What we're looking for:

Knowledge of test data management, data privacy, and handling sensitive information
Strong Project Management acumen including current state analysis ans Business case preparation experience 
Vendor coordination and multi-platform integration experience
Ability to define strategy, standards, and execution plans in low-maturity contexts
Strong stakeholder engagement and problem-solving skills
Comfortable operating with limited internal SME support.
For more information please reach out to Max at mpower@sharpandcarter.com.au

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Senior Data Manager

Location: Sydney, NSW

Security: Baseline clearance minimum (NV1 preferred)

We are seeking a Senior Data Manager to lead data governance, integrity, and analytics for a major Defence transformation program focused on maritime sustainment and operational excellence. This pivotal role ensures secure, accurate, and accessible data to support decision-making across engineering, logistics, and sustainment operations. You will work closely with program leaders, technical teams, and senior stakeholders to establish robust data management frameworks and champion best practices in data integrity and configuration control.

Key Responsibilities:

Define, analyse, and report on data requirements across multiple business domains
Lead data remediation and preparation across program tranches to meet ERP and business requirements
Develop and implement data governance policies, quality metrics, and monitoring procedures
Build team capability in data management, including forecasting risks and planning remediation activities
Align data work packages with organisational objectives and program priorities
Manage data preparation reports and quality improvement plans to ensure migration and conversion readiness

Essential Requirements:

Bachelor's degree or higher in IT, Data Science, Computer Science, Business Information Systems, Engineering, or related field

Company description:



Snowy Hydro is a dynamic, integrated energy business that has been providing on-demand, reliable energy to Australia for generations. Snowy Hydro owns and operates a powerful combination of generation assets, including the mighty Snowy Mountains Scheme, gas and diesel plants, and contracted wind and solar energy. We also provide electricity and gas to about 1.5 million retail customers through our retail brands Red Energy and Lumo Energy.

A full-time position exists for a Senior Strategic Analyst - Hydro to join the Strategy Team in the Planning and Performance stream.



Job description:



The Senior Strategic Analyst - Hydro will lead the ongoing performance and capability of Snowy Hydro's assets and operations and support strategic decision making to ensure we maintain our position and capability in a rapidly changing market. The role adds value by providing strategic perspective and analytical support for decision making processes associated with asset and operations strategy development, risk management and investment decision making. The Strategy Team supports key decision making inputs by linking technical engineering, operations, commercial and work execution strategies. This includes the development of requirements statements, asset life cycle models, and facility strategies to support the overarching Generation Business Plan. This includes extensive stakeholder engagement and front end communication across the business.

Snowy's Hydro portfolio includes 8 Power Stations, 33 Units and ~4.1GW of capacity across the Snowy Mountains, not including the 2.2GW Snowy 2.0 project. This role will be pivotal in informing the strategy for our assets and operations as we manage the challenges of a mixed portfolio of aging and new assets and changing market and operating context.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead the development of the Generation Business Plan to ensure we're planned and ready to deliver our corporate objectives.
Lead the development of Facility Strategies underpinned by life cycle and risk models to support capability, opportunities and investment plans.
Provide a key interface between technical engineering teams, strategy, planning and work execution teams to provide delivery assurance.
Help the business identity and realise value adding opportunities across our assets and operations.
Lead broader business decision making through ad-hoc analysis and decision making support.
Collaborating with others to ensure the Strategic team can extract the information needed for investment decision-making, life cycle costing, and setting long-term delivery strategies.

About the location:

This role offers flexibility in location, with the opportunity to be based in our Cooma, Sydney, or Melbourne office (with a strong preference for Cooma). Relocation support will be offered for anyone wanting to relocate to Cooma. You will be supporting and collaborating with multidisciplinary teams across the business to achieve shared strategic objectives.

About you:

We're looking for a self-starter with a proven industry background, a firm understanding of asset and risk management and an understanding of high criticality operating and commercial environments. You'll need to be able to blend the need to provide strategic thinking, leading analysis, stakeholder engagement and communication. This is not a technical role however a strong understanding of electrical, mechanical and civil assets in heavy industries is integral.

The person we are looking for should have the following capabilities:

An accomplished professional with a background (10+ years is ideal) in asset and business strategy, particularly within dynamic sectors like utilities, heavy industries, or mining.
Broad experience in hydro power generation will be highly regarded.
A sound technical understanding of generation or similar heavy assets (engineering or trade background preferred)
A strong foundation in a business-related discipline (such as a tertiary qualification in commerce, engineering, or CA/CPA or equivalent).
A solid management reporting background alongside demonstrated analytical skills and proficiency in data manipulation.
Demonstrated leadership, excellent stakeholder engagement, and a collaborative approach.
Strong verbal and written communication skills are essential, you'll regularly be engaging with stakeholders from all parts of the business.
The ability to draw meaningful conclusions while working in the grey area.
Capable of working autonomously and meeting deadlines.

About our workforce:

Diversity and inclusion is important to us. Snowy Hydro has a culture of decency and inclusion, with a commitment to the health and wellbeing of our people and a supportive environment to ensure that everyone - regardless of background - feels included and can succeed. At Snowy Hydro, we recognise that we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each individual brings, and we believe in providing an environment that allows that uniqueness to thrive.

Snowy Hydro is proud to be an Equal Opportunity employer. We are committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provide accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. The role in one line (okay... maybe more than one line)

Build and own the AI engine that powers a fast‑moving wholesale operation – from warehouse floor to sales pipeline – turning messy, manual processes into a single, living “source of truth” that everyone can see, trust and act on.

What you’ll be doing
Audit, map, improve. Spend your first 30 days embedded with sales, operations and logistics, pulling apart workflows, spotting “time leaks” and designing AI‑driven fixes that actually ship, not sit in slide decks.
Build the “Dashboard of Truth.” Design and deploy real‑time dashboards (Power BI/custom) wired into Harmonic ERP so every role has a live scorecard, clear KPIs, and forward‑looking trends instead of rear‑view reports.
Supercharge sales and logistics. Create tools that point sales to the right customers at the right time, and help logistics move high‑volume perishables with maximum speed, minimal waste and fewer surprises.
Tame the wild GPTs. Take DIY AI tools created by managers, and rebuild them into a secure, governed, shared framework using Confluence and centralised AI services – same creativity, less chaos.
Own the wholesale ChatBot. Design, build and continuously train a 24/7 client ChatBot that can answer complex product, availability and logistics questions without losing the human tone the brand is known for.
Be the “Tomorrow Team.” Scan the AI landscape, experiment with new tools, and bring only the ones that move real metrics – efficiency, margin, accuracy, customer experience – into production.
The kind of person this will suit
Fluent in “business” and “code.” You can sit in a sales meeting, hear a vague problem, and translate it into data models, workflows and prompts – then go away and quietly make it real.
Hands‑on builder. Comfortable in Python for AI/automation, SQL for getting clean data out of the ERP, and Power BI (or similar) for turning that into visual narratives teams actually use.
Systems thinker. You see end‑to‑end flows across sales, inventory, operations and finance, and design AI interventions that work across the whole system, not just one screen.
Logistics‑curious. You don’t need flower experience, but high‑volume, time‑sensitive product and the puzzle of getting it to the right client at exactly the right moment genuinely excites you.
High‑energy starter. You like being the first in, building a function almost from scratch, setting standards, and proving value quickly with visible wins.
What’s on offer
Real ownership. This isn’t “internal IT” or “BI reporting.” You’ll architect the AI and data layer that underpins how the entire business sells, buys, moves and serves.
Salary on offer. Circa $100 - $120k + super but open to discussion for the "AI guru"
Flex that respects adults. Full‑time role with genuine flexibility in hours and location, plus a regular in‑person rhythm: weekly team time and quarterly strategy days in West Leederville.
Strategy seat. You’ll be at the table for quarterly strategy, shaping how AI supports growth, customer experience and operational excellence over the next 3–5 years.
Industry with heart. You’ll be working in an environment built around creativity, relationships and helping floral businesses thrive – with a team that cares about partnership as much as product.
How to know if you should throw your hat in

If you’ve ever looked at a business and thought, “With clean data, a couple of well‑chosen models, and some decent dashboards, this place would run completely differently,” this is your blank canvas.

Tell me (briefly) about one workflow you transformed with data or AI, what it looked like before, what you built, and the measurable shift it created. Then attach your CV and hit apply.

If you have some questions before applying feel free to call me, Andrew (the guy up the top of the ad) on 08 6140 1800 and we can have a confidential chat.

Job Title: Senior Data Engineer - Data Intelligence - Data ProductsNew
Ad Text:
Join us on our mission to make a better world of work. 

Culture Amp is the world’s leading employee experience platform, revolutionizing how 25 million employees across more than 6,500 companies create a better world of work. Culture Amp empowers companies of all sizes and industries to transform employee engagement, drive performance management, and develop high-performing teams. Powered by people science and the most comprehensive employee dataset in the world, the most innovative companies including Canva, On, Asana, Dolby, McDonalds and Nasdaq depend on Culture Amp every day.

Culture Amp is backed by leading venture capital funds and has offices in the US, UK, Germany and Australia. Culture Amp has been recognized as one of the world’s top private cloud companies by Forbes and most innovative companies by Fast Company.

For more information visit cultureamp.com.

How you can help make a better world of work

We're building the analytics foundation for Culture Amp's next generation of workforce insights. This is a hands-on Senior Data Engineer role in our Data Products team, focused on data modelling and analytical query design at scale.

What you'll do

You'll design and build the data models that power insights connecting engagement, performance, hierarchy and retention data. The goal is helping leaders understand not just what's happening in their organisation, but why.

This means:

Building analytical data models in ClickHouse, optimised for complex queries across millions of survey responses and workforce events
Designing schemas and transformations that make it easy to compute insights across multiple data domains
Collaborating with data scientists to bring statistical and ML models into production
Working with streaming data pipelines (Kafka) to ensure data lands in the right shape for analytical workloads

What makes this interesting

This work is central to Culture Amp's product strategy. We have one of the largest workforce datasets in the world: years of engagement surveys, performance cycles, and organisational changes across thousands of companies. The technical challenge is making that data queryable, joinable, and useful for insights that actually matter to customers.

Job Title

Contract until 30 June

Leading end-to-end process improvement and transformation initiatives within telecommunications environments

Conducting root cause analysis, process mapping, value stream analysis, and benefits quantification

Partnering with senior stakeholders to shape scope, define requirements, and build delivery roadmaps

Facilitating workshops and working sessions to drive alignment and momentum

Producing clear insights, recommendations, and implementation plans

Supporting change adoption across operational and enterprise customer-facing functions

Ensuring delivery aligns to strategic objectives and improves performance, cost, or customer experience

Essential Requirements

Applications will only be considered if you meet all of the following:

Currently based in Sydney, NSW

Lean Six Sigma Black Belt, with demonstrated experience leading real-world improvement programs

Telecommunications industry experience, ideally within one or both of the following domains:

Network operations

Track record delivering measurable outcomes in operational excellence, transformation, or continuous improvement

Desirable

Department of Communities and Justice



Job description:



Manager Standardised Evaluation Analysis

Location - Parramatta/Hybrid working (or another DCJ office location, with some self-funded travel to Parramatta required).

Employment type - Temporary full-time role up to 30 June 2028

Salary - $149,739.00 pa - $173,174.00 pa, plus employer's contribution to superannuation and annual leave loading

About the role

The Manager, Standardised Evaluation Analysis (StEvAn) will oversee and manage the delivery of the StEvAn on behalf of the NSW Government.

Part of the NSW Government Actuary, the StEvAn is the NSW Government's sophisticated and innovative new approach to human services evaluation to build the evidence base for what works.

What you'll do

The successful candidate will be required to manage the StEvAn team and overarching project to deliver outcome evaluation result for a variety of programs and initiatives. It will require a combination of technical skills in evaluation along with superior project management skills. Familiarity with Python and database design is important as this role will require the ability to span the full spectrum of the standardised evaluation process from conventional outcome evaluation design, database management through to overseeing the implementation of the analysis software code which has been designed in house.

The role is responsible for overseeing outcome evaluation design, data analysis, and reporting, ensuring methodological rigour, data integrity, and alignment with governance and strategic priorities. It provides expert advice to senior stakeholders, translating complex findings into clear, actionable insights.

The Manager also leads and develops a technically-diverse team of analysts, driving best practice, continuous improvement, and a collaborative, high-performing culture while working closely with stakeholders to strengthen evaluation capability and outcomes.

The role has a whole-of-government remit. It is part of the NSW Government Actuary, a specialist team of about 30 analysts and evaluation professionals.

What we're looking for

In addition to the essential requirements outlined in the role description, the ideal candidate for the Manager, Standardised Evaluation Analysis role will bring a strong blend of technical expertise, project management, strategic thinking, and people leadership.

They will demonstrate intermediate to advanced capability in Python programming and database design, with a proven ability to develop, manage, and optimise evaluation frameworks and analytical pipelines. The candidate will have experience in evaluation design, including defining metrics, ensuring methodological rigour, and translating complex data into clear, actionable insights for diverse stakeholders.

The ideal candidate will be capable of leading multiple workstreams, setting clear priorities, managing risks, and delivering outcomes within agreed timeframes. They will be comfortable working in complex environments, balancing competing demands while maintaining a strong focus on quality, consistency, and governance.

As a people leader, they will foster a collaborative, inclusive, and high-performing team culture. They will be skilled at mentoring and developing staff, promoting best practice, and driving continuous improvement in analytical capability and processes.

Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills are essential. The candidate will be able to confidently present findings, influence decision-making, and build productive relationships across technical and non-technical audiences.

Above all, the ideal candidate will be self-motivated, outcomes-focused, and committed to continuous improvement, with a strong sense of accountability and a passion for using data and evaluation to support evidence-based decision-making.
